cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses issues related to digital preservation of scientific results, including primary data and published articles, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the preservation and management of digital content. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also relevant as they deal with the storage and retrieval of data. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible as they may address issues related to data privacy and ethical considerations in data preservation and access.
